funcs.name: get_failed_hosts
ret_exprs: return dict((host, True) for (host, state) in iteritems(self._host_states) if self._check_failed_state(state))

docstring.func: Finds the task in the task list which matches the UUID of the given task.
docstring.long_descr:
The executor engine serializes/deserializes objects as they are passed through
the different processes, and not all data structures are preserved. This method
allows us to find the original task passed into the executor engine.
